2 Úlairë Attëa, Keeper of Dol Guldur<br>
2 Úlairë Enquëa, Lieutenant of Morgul<br>
2 Úlairë Cantëa, Lieutenant of Dol Guldur<br>
3 Úlairë Nelya, Lieutenant of Morgul<br>
2 Úlairë Toldëa, Messenger of Morgul<br>
3 <a href="javascript:card_browser(100)">All Blades Perish</a> <br>
3 <a href="javascript:card_browser(112)">Morgul Gates</a><br>
4 <a href="javascript:card_browser(103)">Black Breath</a><br>
3 <a href="javascript:card_browser(104)">Blade Tip</a><br>
1 <a href="javascript:card_browser(130)">Wreathed in Shadow</a><br>
3 <a href="javascript:card_browser(116)">The Pale Blade</a><br>
    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Papy, Times, serif" class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="  Times, Times New Roman, serif" class="bfont"> INTRO<BR>This deck relies on Legolas shooting every minions that hit the table, Gimli killing the remnants and of course Gandalf supporting fellowship crusade with major spells. Use Nine Riders to explain your opponent, that he really don&#39;t need to move more than one site per turn.<BR><BR>TOP CARDS<BR>Legolas, Greenleaf to kill most of opponents minions in archery phase. Gandalf, Friend of the Shirefolk to fight the remnants of minions and cast spells. Elrond, Lord of Rivendell to draw more cards, because the deck has 64 cards. Especially useful is Strength of Spirit - a common spell that lets characters to exert even more ( Legolas to wound minions, Gimli to enhance strength, Aragorn to make him defender +1 also for Sting and Glamdring&#39;s abilities ). Wizard Is Never Late helps with getting Gandalf, Albert Dreary and Barliman to the table. Gimli&#39;s Helm helps to deal with big minions such as Troll, Witch-king or Lurtz. Give Gimli also his Axe and he&#39;s the force to be reckoned with. Aragorn, Ranger of the North is deadly against Moria Swarm.<BR><BR>HOW IT BEATS YOU<BR>Bid 2 burdens and choose to go second. This way your opponent will have to go through nasty Weatherhills and Ford of Bruinen.If Thror&#39;s Map is deployed and opponent decides to go past his sites use Ulaire Nelya to switch back to Nazgul-friendly sites. Going two sites is sometimes needed, but don&#39;t hurry and just follow opponent. Nazgul will kill or stop his companions - there&#39;s no other way. Use allies to direct game in your way - discard Goblin Armory, Goblin Swarms and Spies of Saruman with Albert Dreary; get back Strength of Spirit&#39;s and Servant of the Secret Fire&#39;s back to hand with Barliman Butterbur. From the 4th site number of minions opponent play will be slowly increasing, until 9 site or his Ring-bearer death. Use Gandalf (12 power with Glamdring and all races in fellowship) and Gimli (8 power, takes only one wound) to stop opponents big guns and Legolas to shoot the rest. 2 Sleep, Caradhras are to deal with nasty shadow conditons (Black Breaths, Under The Watchin Eye, Orc Bowmen, etc.). On the shadow side, just play a Nazgul or two each turn and support them with Black Breath/Blade Tip trickery. Witch-king with Pale Blade will kill some characters for sure, don&#39;t forget to get rid of nasty Free Peoples conditions when he wins skirmish (The Saga of Elendil, The Tale of Gil-Galad, No Stranger To The Shadows, The Last Alliance of Elves and Men, etc.). Andin Wilderland (7th site that skips archery phase) is usually an end of a trip for opponent.<BR><BR>NUMBER 1 CARD<BR>All Blades Perish lets you prevent wounds to Nazgul at any time. It deals with the archery trouble - the only Nazgul weakness - for example - opponent exerts with Legolas or Aragorn&#39;s Bow to kill annoying Ringwraith and when the last wound is prevented he has to skirmish the Black Rider using wounded companions !<br><br>Dominik Jastrzebski                         </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP" COLSPAN="2"><font face="  Times, Times New Roman, serif" class="bfont"> <a href="/lotr/decks/decks.php">Back to Decks Directory</a> | <A HREF="/lotr/decks/decks.php?reviews=21114"> Read Reviews </A> | <a href="deckprint.php?deck=21114" TARGET="BLANK_"> Printer Friendly</a></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE><a name="review"></a><font face="Papy, Times, serif" class="h2font">In order to review decks you must be a registered member. <A href="/lotr/main/join.php">Sign up for free!</A></font></font></td></tr></table></td></tr></table> <!-- #EndEditable --></td>
